Asymmetric Encryption + SHA + HMAC

Step 1: Install OpenSSL

	sudo apt update
	sudo apt install openssl


PART 1: Asymmetric Encryption (RSA)

	# Create a private key (2048 bits)
	openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -out private_key.pem -pkeyopt rsa_keygen_bits:2048

	# Extract public key from private key
	openssl rsa -pubout -in private_key.pem -out public_key.pem

private_key.pem → RSA Private Key

public_key.pem → RSA Public Key

Step 3: Create a Message File

	echo "Hello Aditya, this is RSA Encryption!" > message.txt

Step 4: Encrypt with Public Key

	openssl rsautl -encrypt -inkey public_key.pem -pubin -in message.txt -out message.enc

message.enc → Encrypted binary file

Step 5: Decrypt with Private Key

	openssl rsautl -decrypt -inkey private_key.pem -in message.enc -out decrypted.txt
	cat decrypted.txt


PART 2: Secure Hashing (SHA256)

Step 1: Create a Sample File to Hash

	echo "This is a file for hashing." > hashfile.txt

Step 2: Generate SHA256 Hash

	openssl dgst -sha256 hashfile.txt


PART 3: HMAC using SHA256

Step 1: Create a Secret Key
	
	echo -n "myHMACsecretKey" > keyfile.key

Step 2: Generate HMAC-SHA256 of the File

	openssl dgst -sha256 -hmac "$(cat keyfile.key)" hashfile.txt


